{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c8bb8c8e-304c-4bc4-86a5-05ed8beea63f","content":"Here are the common options:\n\n**Templates:**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for REST APIs\n- **ASP.NET Core Minimal API** (`dotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis`) — lightweight, fewer abstractions\n- **FastAPI** (Python), **Express** (Node.js) — non-.NET alternatives\n\n**Authentication options for `dotnet new webapi`:**\n| Flag | Type |\n|------|------|\n| `--auth None` | No auth (default) |\n| `--auth Individual` | Individual user accounts (ASP.NET Identity) |\n| `--auth IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C |\n| `--auth SingleOrg` | Azure AD (single tenant) |\n| `--auth MultiOrg` | Azure AD (multi-tenant) |\n| `--auth Windows` | Windows/Negotiate auth |\n\n**Quick start example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually to any template via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`. Would you like help setting up a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d6318514-7163-4e88-94c5-9a84c96caa55","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context) or web development in general. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to search the codebase, as this is a general development question.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":371,"requestId":"2815:3787BB:127508:184154:69FFD79B"},"id":"a5d70390-82d8-4dd1-983e-a8a22f92c8b3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:56:03.426Z","parentId":"60627b03-0210-429c-a943-74852bbe62e1"}
